  "topic_name": "Force",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Force is a push or pull that can change the state of motion or shape of an object. Forces can cause objects to start moving, stop moving, speed up, slow down, or change direction. Forces are classified as contact forces (requiring physical contact like friction, tension, normal force) and non-contact forces (acting at a distance like gravity, magnetic force, electrostatic force). The SI unit of force is Newton (N). When multiple forces act on an object, they can be balanced (no change in motion) or unbalanced (causes change in motion).",
    "rules": [
      "Force is a push or pull on an object.",
      "Force can change the state of motion of an object.",
      "Force can change the shape of an object.",
      "Contact forces require physical touch: friction, tension, normal force.",
      "Non-contact forces act at a distance: gravity, magnetic, electrostatic.",
      "SI unit of force is Newton (N).",
      "F = ma (Force = mass × acceleration)",
      "Balanced forces result in no change in motion.",
      "Unbalanced forces cause change in motion."
    ]
  },
